{% extends "layouts/doc-layout" %}

{% block title %}Upcase Filter - Wisp Template Documentation{% end %}

{% block body %}
<h1>Upcase Filter</h1>

<p>Converts all characters in a string to uppercase.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% "string" | upcase %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>

<h2>Examples</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% "hello" | upcase %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> HELLO</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% "Hello, World! 123" | upcase %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> HELLO, WORLD! 123</p>
<p>Numbers and symbols are not affected — only alphabetic characters are converted.</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% .category | upcase | truncate: 15 %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> the uppercased category name, truncated to 15 characters</p>
<p>Filters can be chained — <code>upcase</code> runs first, then <code>truncate</code> operates on the result.</p>

<h2>Notes</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Numbers, punctuation, and symbols in the string are passed through unchanged.</li>
  <li>Use <code>upcase</code> for display purposes (e.g., labels, headings) or to normalize strings for comparison.</li>
</ul>

<h2>See Also</h2>
<ul>
  <li><a href="/docs/filters/capitalize">capitalize</a></li>
  <li><a href="/docs/filters/downcase">downcase</a></li>
</ul>
{% end %}
